  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Take your<strong> lamb leg joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into quarters, then add to a pot (with a matching lid) with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677845765456-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677845765456-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677845765456-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677845765456-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677845765456-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min, then drain (save the pot!) and shake them around the colander to fluff up the edges</p><p>While the potatoes are boiling, strip the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Top, tail, peel and cut the <strong>carrots</strong> into batons</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677845772615-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677845772615-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677845772615-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677845772615-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677845772615-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray<strong> </strong>with <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chopped rosemary</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then put the tray in the oven for 30-35 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>roasties</strong></p><p>Reboil the kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677845784663-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677845784663-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677845784663-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677845784663-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677845784663-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the string from the <strong>lamb leg joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub the <strong>lamb</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and season with the <strong>remaining chopped rosemary</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned lamb</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until browned on all sides</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677845795969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677845795969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677845795969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677845795969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677845795969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer it to a baking tray and reserve the pan</p><p>Once the potatoes have been cooking for 20 min, put the tray with the lamb in the oven for 8-9 min for rare, 10-12 min for medium-rare and 12-14 min for medium</p><p>Once the lamb is cooked, transfer it to a clean chopping board to rest for 3 min before slicing – this is your<strong> roast lamb</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677845808530-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677845808530-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677845808530-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677845808530-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677845808530-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lamb is cooking, dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>red wine paste</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>beef stock</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and once melted, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and mix until a paste forms, then whisk in the <strong>beef stock </strong>and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>red wine gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677845813311-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677845813311-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677845813311-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677845813311-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677845813311-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot batons</strong> with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 7-8 min or until the carrot is tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once tender, add the <strong>blanched peas</strong> and<strong> half</strong> the <strong>mint sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!) and stir until warmed through – these are your <strong>minty peas & carrots</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677845818086-x200.jpg",
